Macquarie County was named in honour of Governor Lachlan Macquarie (1762-1824).

Macquarie County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales , Australia . It is bordered to the north by the Apsley River, and to the south by the Manning River . It includes Port Macquarie and the area around it.
